			<h2>Correspondence</h2>
			<a class="xsmall link-alt" href="https://www.thesunmagazine.org/letter-to-the-editor">Write a Letter to the Editor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>
		</div>

		<div id="article-correspondences" class="correspondences correspondences-collapsed">
								<div class="block-correspondence" id="1614">
		<blockquote class="quote-2">
			<p>I have in the past found the tuneful ruminations of Sparrow quite welcome and often profound in their simplicity, but his essay &ldquo;<a href="/article/4344">Spring Comes to New Jersey</a>&rdquo; [October 2009] is close to mere &ldquo;twittering.&rdquo; To the editors (you do still have editors there, I presume): by all means, keep the Sparrow coming, but sift out just the gold nuggets, please.</p>
							<p class="quote-2-author">Jerome Szymczak<br>Alameda, California</p>
					</blockquote>
	</div>

					</div>

